        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2574552812" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2519773213738850628">An exhausting book to read, the writing covers a diverse array of fields. Different diets, food preparations, animals, modes of transport, forms of currency, royalty, religions, races and more. This is all terribly consistently punctuated by footnotes giving details of other translators, Arabic quotes &amp; similar. <br/><br/>Ibn Battuta himself was a peripatetic in the extreme. One does ponder if he had been rather more a mendicant &amp; less an emissary would he have gone so far? The gifts, (temporary) marriage</span>
  <span id="freeText2519773213738850628" style="display:none">An exhausting book to read, the writing covers a diverse array of fields. Different diets, food preparations, animals, modes of transport, forms of currency, royalty, religions, races and more. This is all terribly consistently punctuated by footnotes giving details of other translators, Arabic quotes &amp; similar. <br /><br />Ibn Battuta himself was a peripatetic in the extreme. One does ponder if he had been rather more a mendicant &amp; less an emissary would he have gone so far? The gifts, (temporary) marriages &amp; relationships with royalty are all past methods of diplomacy. There is some fantastic sections of this book, Rokh birds &amp; sea-horses are all that comes to mind. <br /><br />His grand tour of the world during the 14th century is the stuff from which legends are made.<br /><br />The book is available free online.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2519773213738850628" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


