              <span id="reviewTextContainer1377646138" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9285336344025061527">A very approachable introduction to one of the world&apos;s greatest travellers. I found Battuta&apos;s viewpoints on the travels most interesting. Marrying, divorcing, parenting as he travelled all were entirely acceptable; brandishing errant slaves also seemed within reason, but visiting a court and not being given money or presents to keep him during his stay was totally wrong!<br/><br/>A must read for any traveller.</span>
  <span id="freeText9285336344025061527" style="display:none">A very approachable introduction to one of the world's greatest travellers. I found Battuta's viewpoints on the travels most interesting. Marrying, divorcing, parenting as he travelled all were entirely acceptable; brandishing errant slaves also seemed within reason, but visiting a court and not being given money or presents to keep him during his stay was totally wrong!<br /><br />A must read for any traveller.</span>
