        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3759747717" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1561507273519580096">This book was interesting and certainly gave me a good look at that part of the world in a much different time; although, the attitudes were the same. Infidels (Christians) were hated and berated. Sigh...<br/><br/>It depicts in turns great detail and a brief overview of places visited, food eaten, transportation methods (horses, camels, wagons, elephants), people met, and places visited. Honestly, it could have been shorter and if so would have kept my attention better. The fascination was primarily the l</span>
  <span id="freeText1561507273519580096" style="display:none">This book was interesting and certainly gave me a good look at that part of the world in a much different time; although, the attitudes were the same. Infidels (Christians) were hated and berated. Sigh...<br /><br />It depicts in turns great detail and a brief overview of places visited, food eaten, transportation methods (horses, camels, wagons, elephants), people met, and places visited. Honestly, it could have been shorter and if so would have kept my attention better. The fascination was primarily the length of the trip. IB started out to make his pilgrimage to Mecca and continued for another 29 years, which is a little crazy but intriguing. How amazing would it be to simply pick up and travel the world for that long? <br /><br />So, the book was interesting, but definitely not recommendation worthy. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1561507273519580096" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
